Hello I'm trying to batch "upsert" with `POST /contacts/v1/contact/batch/` API (cuz v3 API doesn't have equivalent).
And I have a one question .

When post contacts those have same email's at same time, which contact property will win ?

<https://knowledge.HubSpot.com/crm-setup/deduplication-of-contacts-companies-deals-tickets|doc about deduplicate> said...
```if a contact already exists in your account with the same email address, the new contact information will be added to the existing contact record```
but actual behavior seems bit different with doc .

for example , when we post contacts shown below

```[
    {
        "email": "<mailto:same@some.com|same@some.com>",
        "properties": [
            {
                "property": "firstname",
                "value": "firstname1"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "email": "<mailto:same@some.com|same@some.com>",
        "properties": [
            {
                "property": "lastname",
                "value": "lastname1"
            },
            {
                "property": "firstname",
                "value": "firstname2"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "email": "<mailto:same@some.com|same@some.com>",
        "properties": [
            {
                "property": "lastname",
                "value": "lastname2"
            },
            {
                "property": "firstname",
                "value": "firstname3"
            }
        ]
    }
]```
finally contact has `firstname1` and  `lastname1` .  seems first contact in array *and*  first contact that set property in array will finally win .

so any defined behavior is existing about this ? or simply undefined? thanks for any help
